cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robot learning for manipulation tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel self-supervision technique for learning complex manipulation tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the method operates atop visual model predictive control and uses uncalibrated RGB camera input. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a learning-based approach for producing robust policies. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with controlling a physical robot to perform assembly tasks.
